description:
&lt;p&gt;Are you a registered Paramedic? Are you looking for an exciting and integral role within The Defence Medical Services (DMS)?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Look no further.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking an experienced and dedicated individual to fulfil the role of Paramedic Instructor here at The Defence Medical Academy (DMA) at Keogh Training Centre.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The purpose of DMA is to provide our Armed Forces with the military medical education and training they require for operations in the 21st Century. Your role as the successful candidate, will be key in facilitating the requirements in Defence School Healthcare Training (DSHT).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will be expected to support the delivery and assist the coordination of Phase 2 training in order to provide Defence Medical Services (DMS) with suitably qualified personnel.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Please refer to the attached Job Description and Person Specification for the role and its requirements in further detail.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Essential Criteria&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Must be a current HCPC registered Paramedic&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please take note of the training competencies criteria on the attached job description.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h1&gt; &lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;Selection Process&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The selection at sift stage will be based on your CV.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please ensure you demonstrate that you have the required skills, knowledge, experience, qualifications and memberships in the CV section of the application form. &lt;strong&gt;Please make sure no personal details are included.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At interview, you will be tested against the following Behaviours and NHS Key Skills Framework:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Leadership&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Seeing the Big Picture&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Delivering at Pace&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Communicating and Influencing&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Working together&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Developing Self and Others&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;NHS General – NHS G1 – Learning &amp; Development&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Travel to interview costs will not be reimbursed.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;Further Information&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Successful candidates must meet the security requirements before they can be appointed. The level of security needed is security check.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;All employees joining Ministry of Defence who are new to the Civil Service will be subject to a 6-month probation period (unless otherwise advised) effective from the employment start date.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please note the salary will be pro-rata where part time hours are undertaken.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Please ensure you have read all the details in the important information link prior to applying.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
